a3DeviceId.name: a3DeviceId
a3DeviceId.description: On systems that implement a PnP-like subsystem, the device ID should be the ID used by that subsystem. On systems that do not have inherent device numbering, then the instrumentation supporting the system resources group should devise a device number scheme. In either case, the table will naturally group all of the resources associated with a device.

a3ResourceNumber.name: a3ResourceNumber
a3ResourceNumber.description: This attribute is the ordinal of the resource within a device. Within the table, any device may have one or more resources.

a3ResourceType.name: a3ResourceType
a3ResourceType.description: The type of system resource represented by this entry.

a3ResourceBase.name: a3ResourceBase
a3ResourceBase.description: The starting address of the system resource in the appropriate address space.

a3ResourceSize.name: a3ResourceSize
a3ResourceSize.description: The size of the system resource.

a3ResourceFlags.name: a3ResourceFlags
a3ResourceFlags.description: This attribute contains fields representing the status of this resource entry. The meaning of this field varies according to the Resource Type field in this group.

a3GroupId.name: a3GroupId
a3GroupId.description: This attribute is a 'back pointer' to a group within this MIF, if applicable. If the back pointer is not known, either because the device is not represented by a group, or the actual device type is not known, then the value of this attribute will be 0.

tNetworkAdapter802PortGroup.name: tNetworkAdapter802PortGroup

a4CurrentNetworkAddress.description: This is the node address that can be modified by software, sometimes referred to as the Locally Administered Address (LAA).

a4TotalWireErrors.name: a4TotalWireErrors
